What's new in Ambulant Player 2.6?
----------------------------------

- This is mainly a cleanup release, incorporating all fixes we have made in the
  last 3 years. It will also probably be the last release with browser plugins.

- Binary (PPA) installers for Linux are available.

- Hooks for distributed synchronisation of presentations.

- Handling of video playback has improved.

- SDL-based player for Linux (especilly for embedding) has been added.

- Framework for recording/retransmitting presentations added.

- Live streaming latency greatly reduced.

- Updated all external packages (gtk, ffmpeg, sdl) to modern versions.

- Preliminary support for Android is available.